From a19e78a7715143e9ad78e3691a70647fb4751b55 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thierry Reding <treding@nvidia.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Feb 2014 08:55:27 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 229/479] drm/i915: Remove dead code

commit d4d5be6192caaee39e40ea7a7017316237ae195f upstream.

The i915 driver sets DRIVER_GEM unconditionally, so testing for the
feature will always fail.

Signed-off-by: Thierry Reding <treding@nvidia.com>
[danvet: Fix up conflicts.]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem_context.c | 6 ------
 1 file changed, 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem_context.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem_context.c
index f8c21a6..da74522 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem_context.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem_context.c
@@ -746,9 +746,6 @@ int i915_gem_context_create_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
 	struct i915_hw_context *ctx;
 	int ret;
 
-	if (!(dev->driver->driver_features & DRIVER_GEM))
-		return -ENODEV;
-
 	if (!HAS_HW_CONTEXTS(dev))
 		return -ENODEV;
 
@@ -775,9 +772,6 @@ int i915_gem_context_destroy_ioctl(struct drm_device *dev, void *data,
 	struct i915_hw_context *ctx;
 	int ret;
 
-	if (!(dev->driver->driver_features & DRIVER_GEM))
-		return -ENODEV;
-
 	if (args->ctx_id == DEFAULT_CONTEXT_ID)
 		return -ENOENT;
 
